# Datasets

This project uses publicly available road damage datasets for training and evaluating the YOLOv8 model.

## Primary Dataset
**RDD2022 (Road Damage Detection 2022)**
- Source: https://github.com/sekilab/RoadDamageDetector
- Contains over 47,000 road images collected from multiple countries.
- Includes potholes, cracks, and other road surface damages with bounding-box annotations.

## Optional Dataset
**Roboflow Pothole Dataset**
- Source: https://universe.roboflow.com/
- Used for additional fine-tuning to improve pothole detection accuracy.

## Purpose
These datasets are used to:
- Train the YOLOv8 object detection model.
- Detect potholes and road surface defects.
- Evaluate model performance under different road conditions.

> **Note:** The actual datasets are not included in this repository due to their large size. They can be downloaded from the above sources.
